    <!-- Application Structure Plan: Dashboard Layout. 
         Rationale: The "110+ Sleep Statistics" report is dense with data. A dashboard with a persistent sidebar allows users to jump between "Demographics", "Health", and "Trends" without losing context. 
         The main content area uses a masonry-style grid to mix quantitative charts with qualitative "Insight Cards" extracted from the text. 
    -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
         1. Global Stats -> Goal: Inform -> Big Number Cards -> No interaction -> High level summary.
         2. Sleep vs Age -> Goal: Compare -> Bar Chart (Chart.js) -> Toggle Age Groups -> Visualizing the "Teen vs Adult" gap.
         3. Disorders -> Goal: Relationships -> Doughnut Chart -> Click to reveal details -> Showing prevalence of Apnea/Insomnia.
         4. Wellness Factors -> Goal: Organize -> Interactive List -> JS Filter -> Connecting stress to sleep quality.
         CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used.
    -->
</head>

